'''Alexandria University''' ({{lang-ar|<U+062C><U+0627><U+0645><U+0639><U+0629> <U+0627><U+0644><U+0625><U+0633><U+0643><U+0646><U+062F><U+0631><U+064A><U+0629>}}) is a public research university in [[Alexandria]], [[Egypt]]. It was established in 1938 as a satellite of [[Cairo University|Fuad University]] (the name of which was later changed to Cairo University), becoming an independent entity in 1942. It was known as Farouk University until the [[Egyptian Revolution of 1952]] when its name was changed to the University of Alexandria. [[Taha Hussein]] was the founding [[Rector (academia)|rector]] of Alexandria University. It is now the second largest university in [[Egypt]] and has many affiliations to various universities for ongoing [[research]].

== Faculties ==
[[File:Alexandria University.JPG|thumb|Administration building, Alexandria University]]

At the time it became an independent institution in 1942, it had the following [[faculty (university)|faculties]]:
* Faculty of [[Agriculture]]
* [[Alexandria Faculty of Medicine|Faculty of Medicine]] (1942)
* Faculty of [[The arts|Arts]] (1938)
* Faculty of [[Commerce]]
* [[Faculty of Engineering, Alexandria University|Faculty of Engineering]] (1941)
* Faculty of [[Law]] (1938)
* [[Faculty of Science, Alexandria University|Faculty of Science]]

A number of institutional entities were established as follows:
* Faculty of Sports Education (1955)
* Faculty of [[Nursing]] (formerly the High Institute of Nursing) (1954)
* Faculty of [[Pharmacy]] (1956)
* High Institute of [[Public Health]] (1963)
* Faculty of [[Education]] (1969)
* [[Alexandria Faculty of Dentistry|Faculty of Dentistry]]: founded in 1971 and serves the city of Alexandria. It is located in El Azareta near the famous [[Bibliotheca Alexandrina|Alexandria Library]].
* [[Medical Research Institute]] (1971)
* [[Faculty of Veterinary Medicine of Alexandria University|Faculty of Veterinary Medicine]] (1974)
* Institute of [[Graduate Studies]] & Research (1983)
* Faculty of [[Tourism]] and [[Hotel]]s (1983)
* Faculty of Finearts
* Faculty of Kindergarten

In 1989, four faculties, located in Alexandria and administered by [[Helwan University]], were annexed to Alexandria University. These are the faculties of [[Agriculture]], [[Fine Arts]], [[Physical Education]] for Boys and Physical Education for Girls.

== Notable Alumni & Faculty ==
* [[Ahmed Zewail]] (Faculty of Science, 1967) <U+2013> Noble Prize in Chemistry 1999.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/1999/|title=The Nobel Prize in Chemistry 1999|publisher=Nobelprize.org|accessdate=2013-02-04}}</ref>
* [[Mohammed Aboul-Fotouh Hassab]] (1913<U+2013>2000) <U+2013> Professor of gastro-intestinal surgery; creator of surgical procedure known as [[Hassab's decongestion operation]]<ref>http://www.annalsgastro.gr/files/journals/1/earlyview/2012/ev-02-2012-10-1464.pdf</ref>
* [[Mohamed Hashish]] (Faculty of Engineering) Research scientist best known as the father of the abrasive water jet cutter.
* [[Yahya El Mashad]] (Faculty of Engineering, 1952) Egyptian nuclear physicist.
* [[Mo Ibrahim]] (Faculty of Engineering) Sudanese-British mobile communications entrepreneur and billionaire.
* [[Abdel-Wahab El-Messiri]] (Faculty of the Arts, 1959) <U+2013> Coordinator of anti-[[Mubarak]] movement [[Kefaya]] (2007<U+2013>2008);
* [[Tawfiq Saleh]] (English literature, 1949) <U+2013> Film director<ref name=ahram>{{cite news|first=|last=|title=Egyptian renowned film director Tawfiq Saleh dies at 87|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/5/32/79335/Arts--Culture/Film/Egyptian-renowned-film-director-Tawfiq-Saleh-dies-.aspx|work=[[Al-Ahram]]|date=2013-08-18|accessdate=2013-09-14}}</ref>

